## RTL Considerations
- Logo is symmetrical, works in both LTR and RTL
- Speech bubble tail remains on right side (standard WhatsApp convention)
- No text in logo, so no RTL flipping needed
- Position logo on left in LTR, right in RTL layouts using CSS logical properties

```css
/* RTL support */
.header[dir="rtl"] .logo {
  margin-left: 1rem;
  margin-right: 0;
}
```

## Accessibility
- SVG includes `aria-label="Wboty Logo"`
- Decorative only, so `role="img"` and `aria-hidden="true"` on container
- Sufficient color contrast in both modes (green on dark/light backgrounds)

## Scalability
- SVG scales perfectly to any size
- For very small sizes (under 24px), consider simplified version without dots
- For print/PDF, ensure CMYK color conversion maintains brand green

## Brand Guidelines Summary
1. **Primary**: Green W with bubble outline + circuit dots
2. **Monochromatic**: Use for grayscale contexts (replace green with dark gray)
3. **Icon-only**: Use simplified W+dots for favicon, app icons
4. **Never**: Stretch, rotate, add effects, or change color proportions

This design maintains WhatsApp brand recognition while establishing Wboty as a professional B2B SaaS tool with AI capabilities.

# Rebranding Rollout Acceptance Criteria & Test Plan

## 1. Acceptance Criteria (Definition of Done)

### ✅ **UI Text Verification**
- [ ] All instances of "WhatsApp Agent" replaced with new brand name in:
  - Page titles (`<title>` tags)
  - Headers (h1-h6)
  - Button labels
  - Form placeholders
  - Tooltips and help text
  - Error/success messages
  - Meta tags (OpenGraph, Twitter)
- [ ] No hardcoded brand references in JavaScript/TypeScript strings
- [ ] Brand name appears correctly in Hebrew (RTL rendering)
- [ ] No broken text truncation due to longer/shorter brand name

### ✅ **Logo Display**
- [ ] New logo displays in all locations:
  - Navigation bar/header
  - Login page
  - Dashboard sidebar
  - Tenant selection screen
  - Favicon (all sizes: 16x16, 32x32, 192x192, 512x512)
  - Email templates (if any)
  - Loading states
- [ ] Logo responsive on all screen sizes (320px - 1920px)
- [ ] Logo maintains aspect ratio and doesn't pixelate
- [ ] Dark/light mode logo variants (if applicable)
- [ ] Logo alt text updated to new brand name

### ✅ **Domain & URL Functionality**
- [ ] New domain resolves correctly
- [ ] All existing routes work under new domain:
  - `/login`
  - `/tenant/[id]/*` subroutes
  - `/api/*` endpoints
- [ ] Supabase auth redirect URLs updated
- [ ] Session cookies work cross-domain (if domain changed)
- [ ] WhatsApp webhook URLs updated in session-manager
- [ ] No mixed content warnings (HTTP/HTTPS)

### ✅ **Regression Protection**
- [ ] **Auth flows unchanged**: login, logout, session refresh
- [ ] **Database schema unchanged**: no migrations, no data loss
- [ ] **WhatsApp functionality intact**: message sending/receiving, AI replies
- [ ] **Session-manager unchanged**: no modifications to Baileys/DeepSeek integration
- [ ] **API contracts unchanged**: all existing API endpoints return same structure
- [ ] **Multi-tenant isolation preserved**: tenant A still cannot access tenant B's data
- [ ] **Filter modes work**: whitelist/blacklist/all still function correctly
- [ ] **Agent modes work**: learning/active/paused transitions unchanged

---

## 2. Test Cases

### **Test Suite 1: UI Text & Logo**
```typescript
// Example Jest test for brand text replacement
describe('Brand Text Replacement', () => {
  test('All pages should show new brand name', async () => {
    // Use Playwright to navigate and check text content
    const page = await browser.newPage();
    await page.goto('/login');

    // Check page title
    const title = await page.title();
    expect(title).toContain('NewBrandName');
    expect(title).not.toContain('WhatsApp Agent');

    // Check main heading
    const heading = await page.locator('h1').textContent();
    expect(heading).toContain('NewBrandName');

    // Check all buttons for old brand references
    const buttons = await page.locator('button').allTextContents();
    buttons.forEach(text => {
      expect(text).not.toContain('WhatsApp Agent');
    });
  });

  test('Logo displays correctly in RTL Hebrew context', async () => {
    // Simulate Hebrew language
    await page.goto('/tenant/123?lang=he');

    // Check logo src attribute
    const logo = await page.locator('img[alt*="NewBrandName"]');
    expect(await logo.getAttribute('src')).toMatch(/new-logo\.(png|svg)/);

    // Verify RTL layout still works with new logo
    const logoStyle = await logo.evaluate(el => getComputedStyle(el));
    expect(logoStyle.direction).toBe('rtl');
  });
});
```

### **Test Suite 2: Multi-tenant Isolation (Critical)**
```typescript
describe('Multi-tenant isolation after rebrand', () => {
  test('Tenant A cannot access Tenant B conversations via API', async () => {
    // Mock two different tenant sessions
    const tenantA = { id: 'tenant-a-uuid', business_name: 'Tenant A' };
    const tenantB = { id: 'tenant-b-uuid', business_name: 'Tenant B' };

    // Attempt to access tenant B's data with tenant A's auth
    const response = await fetch(`/api/tenants/${tenantB.id}/messages`, {
      headers: { 'Authorization': `Bearer ${tenantAToken}` }
    });

    expect(response.status).toBe(403); // Should still be forbidden
    expect(await response.json()).toHaveProperty('error', 'Unauthorized');
  });

  test('Tenant list only shows current user tenants', async () => {
    // User should only see their tenants, not all tenants in system
    const page = await browser.newPage();
    await loginAsUser(page, 'user1@example.com');

    const tenantCards = await page.locator('.tenant-card').count();
    const tenantNames = await page.locator('.tenant-name').allTextContents();

    // User should only see their assigned tenants
    expect(tenantNames).toEqual(['Tenant A', 'Tenant C']); // Not Tenant B
  });
});
```

### **Test Suite 3: Hebrew/RTL Support**
```typescript
describe('Hebrew RTL support with new branding', () => {
  test('Hebrew text renders correctly with new logo', async () => {
    await page.goto('/tenant/123');

    // Set Hebrew content
    await page.evaluate(() => {
      document.documentElement.lang = 'he';
      document.documentElement.dir = 'rtl';
    });

    // Check RTL layout
    const container = await page.locator('.chat-container');
    const style = await container.evaluate(el => getComputedStyle(el));
    expect(style.direction).toBe('rtl');
    expect(style.textAlign).toBe('right');

    // Logo should still be visible and properly positioned
    const logo = await page.locator('header img');
    const logoPosition = await logo.evaluate(el => {
      const rect = el.getBoundingClientRect();
      return { left: rect.left, right: rect.right };
    });

    // In RTL, logo should be on the right side
    expect(logoPosition.right).toBeLessThan(window.innerWidth);
    expect(logoPosition.left).toBeGreaterThan(window.innerWidth / 2);
  });

  test('Mixed Hebrew/English brand text', async () => {
    // Test brand name appears correctly in mixed language contexts
    const page = await browser.newPage();
    await page.setContent(`
      <div dir="rtl" lang="he">
        <h1>ברוכים הבאים ל-<span class="brand">NewBrandName</span></h1>
        <p>המערכת שלך לניהול וואטסאפ</p>
      </div>
    `);

    const brandElement = await page.locator('.brand');
    expect(await brandElement.textContent()).toBe('NewBrandName');

    // Brand should maintain LTR within RTL context
    const brandStyle = await brandElement.evaluate(el => getComputedStyle(el));
    expect(brandStyle.direction).toBe('ltr');
    expect(brandStyle.unicodeBidi).toBe('embed');
  });
});
```

### **Test Suite 4: WhatsApp Functionality Regression**
```typescript
describe('WhatsApp functionality unchanged', () => {
  test('AI still replies in active mode', async () => {
    // Simulate incoming WhatsApp message
    const webhookResponse = await fetch('/api/webhook', {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
      body: JSON.stringify({
        tenantId: 'test-tenant',
        phone: '972501234567',
        message: 'שלום, מה השעות שלכם?'
      })
    });

    expect(webhookResponse.status).toBe(200);

    // Check AI response was generated (via DeepSeek mock)
    expect(mockOpenAI.chat.completions.create).toHaveBeenCalled();

    // Response should be in Hebrew
    const response = await webhookResponse.json();
    expect(response.reply).toMatch(/[\u0590-\u05FF]/); // Hebrew characters
  });

  test('Learning mode still stores messages without replying', async () => {
    // Set tenant to learning mode
    await updateTenantMode('test-tenant', 'learning');

    // Send message
    const webhookResponse = await fetch('/api/webhook', {
      method: 'POST',
      body: JSON.stringify({/* test message */})
    });

    // Should store but not reply
    expect(webhookResponse.status).toBe(200);
    const data = await webhookResponse.json();
    expect(data.reply).toBeNull();

    // Verify message stored in database
    const messages = await supabase
      .from('messages')
      .select('*')
      .eq('tenant_id', 'test-tenant');

    expect(messages.data).toHaveLength(1);
  });
});
```

---

## 3. Edge Cases & Risk Areas

### **Critical Edge Cases:**
1. **Mixed branding during cache transition** - Users might see old brand if CDN cache not cleared
2. **Bookmarked URLs with old domain** - Should redirect to new domain
3. **Email notifications with old branding** - Check transactional emails
4. **API clients using old User-Agent strings** - Should still work
5. **Hebrew brand name with special characters** - Test Unicode handling

### **Performance Considerations:**
- Logo file size should not increase page load time
- No additional network requests for branding assets
- CSS/JS bundle size unchanged (branding should be compile-time replacement)

### **Mobile-Specific Tests:**
- Logo displays correctly on mobile viewports (320px width)
- Touch targets around logo still work
- No horizontal scrolling introduced by new logo size

---

## 4. Regression Checklist

### **Verify These Still Work:**
- [ ] Tenant onboarding flow
- [ ] WhatsApp connection process (QR code display)
- [ ] Real-time message updates via Supabase
- [ ] Contact filter rules (whitelist/blacklist)
- [ ] Knowledge base management
- [ ] Agent mode switching
- [ ] Message search/filter
- [ ] Export conversations
- [ ] User profile/settings

### **Verify No Changes To:**
- [ ] Database schema (run `SELECT * FROM information_schema.tables`)
- [ ] API response formats (compare OpenAPI/Swagger spec)
- [ ] Authentication tokens/JWT structure
- [ ] WhatsApp webhook payload format
- [ ] Session-manager environment variables
- [ ] Build process (`npm run build` output)

---

